1 assessed and paid annually. Upon initial registration of a vehicle, the fees shall be assessed
2 based upon the date of sale.
3 Section 2. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 32-5:
4 The license fees applicable to a noncommercial trailer registered in this state,
5 pursuant to § 32-5-8, which has an actual weight of three thousand pounds or less, are
6 one-time fees paid only upon the owner's initial registration of the trailer and may not be
7 assessed annually.
8 The registration is valid for the useful life of the trailer, unless:
9 (a) The actual weight of the trailer exceeds three thousand pounds, in which case the
10 trailer is subject to an annual assessment of license fees, as provided in § 32-5-8,
11 based on the new actual weight; or
12 (b) Title to the trailer is transferred, in which case the new owner must, within forty-
13 five days after the transfer, register the trailer and pay the one-time license fees,
14 as provided in § 32-5-8.
